gluon–gluon fusion:  The ggF production is accurate to NNLO in QCD, using the Powheg method [41] for matching the matrix element with the parton shower, and the MiNLO method [42, 43] to simultaneously achieve NLO accuracy for inclusive Higgs boson production. Furthermore, a reweighting procedure was performed using the HNNLO program [44–46] to achieve full NNLO accuracy [47]. This sample is referred to as NNLOPS. The PDF4LHC15 NLO PDF set [48] was used. The inclusive cross section of the ggF production is normalised to the calculation at next-to-next-to-next-to-leading-order (N3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
