				\begin{document}$$pp$$\end{document} collisions in each bunch crossing, “pile-up”, were simulated with the soft QCD processes of Pythia 8.186 using the A2 tune [63] and the MSTW2008LO PDF set [64]. An additional event-level reweighting is performed in order to ensure that the distribution of the average number of interactions per bunch crossing matches that occurring in the data used in this analysis. The particles in the final states of the generated processes were passed through either a Geant4  [65] simulation of the ATLAS detector, or through the ATLAS fast simulation framework [66], which has been extensively validated against the Geant4 simulation model. The output from the detector simulation is then analysed using the same reconstruction software as the data. The MC samples for single-Higgs-boson production were simulated with the Geant4 framework, while the other samples used in this analysis were produced with the ATLAS fast simulation framework.

