				\begin{document}$$\gamma \gamma \ell \nu jj$$\end{document} and the reducible processes represented by events where one or two hadronic jets are misidentified as photons. The reducible processes are modelled by the data events with reversed photon identification or isolation requirements. The two components are combined according to the measured diphoton purity, which is about 88% (90% with pTγγ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
